=== 投票规则 ===
2018年国际足联世界杯和2022年国际足联世界杯的投票被安排在了一起进行，主办国通过{{link-en|多轮绝对多数制|Exhaustive ballot}}的方法决定出。所有国际足联理事会的成员均拥有1票，每轮投票中获得最少票数的申办主张将遭到淘汰，直至选出票数最多的主办国。当出现票数相等的情况时，时任国际足联主席[[塞普·布拉特]]将拥有一票决定权。当时参与投票的国际足联理事会的成员共有24个，然而其中2个成员被指受贿，被取消了投票权。曾一度传出流言称将重新投票，然而最终并未实行<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2010/SPORT/football/12/02/football.world.cup.2018.2022/index.html?hpt=T1|title=Russia, Qatar win race to host World Cups as FIFA spreads its vision|date=2010-11-02|language=en|publisher=CNN|accessdate=2018-08-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180814170251/http://www.cnn.com/2010/SPORT/football/12/02/football.world.cup.2018.2022/index.html?hpt=T1|archive-date=2018-08-14|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://sports.qq.com/a/20150603/054687.htm |title=曝2018和2022年世界杯恐重新投票 中国举办？ |publisher=[[腾讯|腾讯新闻]] |accessdate=2018-08-14 |date=2015-06-03 |language=zh-hans }}</ref>。当某一轮投票中某个国家获得了12个选票以上，将被直接认定为主办国<ref name=ruleandend>{{cite news|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/bidders/2018/media/newsid=1344971.html |title=Russia and Qatar to host 2018 and 2022 FIFA World Cups, respectively |publisher=[[国际足联]] |language=en |date=2010-12-02 |accessdate=2018-08-15 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101203003635/http://www.fifa.com/worldcup/bidders/2018/media/newsid%3D1344971.html |archivedate=2010-12-03 |deadurl=no }}</ref>。

=== 投票结果 ===
2010年12月2日，时任国际足联主席[[塞普·布拉特]]在[[苏黎世]]的国际足联总部宣布了2018年和2022年国际足联世界杯的主办国家。[[俄罗斯]]被选为[[2018年国际足联世界杯]]主办国，[[卡塔尔]]被选为[[2022年国际足联世界杯]]主办国<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/russia2018/news/newsid=1344698/index.html |title=Russia and Qatar awarded 2018 and 2022 FIFA World Cups |date=2010-12-02 |publisher=[[国际足联]] |accessdate=2018-08-15 |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141109235844/http://www.fifa.com/worldcup/russia2018/news/newsid=1344698/index.html |archive-date=2014-11-09 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。这使得俄罗斯成为了第一个举办世界杯的[[东欧]]国家，卡塔尔成为了第一个举办世界杯的[[中东]]国家<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2010/dec/02/england-russia-win-2018-world-cup |title=England beaten as Russia win 2018 World Cup bid |date=2010-12-02 |work=The Guardian |location=London |accessdate=2018-08-15 |first=Owen |last=Gibson |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180616195649/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2010/dec/02/england-russia-win-2018-world-cup |archive-date=2018-06-16 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2010/dec/02/qatar-win-2022-world-cup-bid |title=Qatar win 2022 World Cup bid |date=2010-12-02 |work=The Guardian |location=London |accessdate=2018-08-15 |first=Jamie |last=Jackson |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180801124948/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2010/dec/02/qatar-win-2022-world-cup-bid |archive-date=2018-08-01 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。布拉特在宣布结果时称，“世界杯走进了新的土地”<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/12/03/sports/soccer/03worldcup.html?_r=1&hp |title=Russia and Qatar Win World Cup Bids |last=Longman |first=Jeré |work=New York Times |accessdate=2018-08-15 |language=en |date=2010-12-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180707090707/https://www.nytimes.com/2010/12/03/sports/soccer/03worldcup.html?_r=1&hp |archive-date=2018-07-07 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

